<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-28T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-28T15:00:00-05:00" n="741" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d741">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2649: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Warren</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-28T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 28,
                                        1922—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>95. Your No. 135, August 9, 1 p.m. and No. 140, August 23, 5 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Suggestion of Japanese Government is today being brought to attention of
                            British, French and Italian Governments.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>